Defendant Joseph A McGinty in court with attorney M. Elizabeth Weathers.  Kevin Michael Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea to the charge. Court finds him guilty and imposed the following sentence:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

30 DAYS HUBER, w/Standard Release Conditions 

TERM OF PROBATION:  6 months;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No violent contact with the victim
*Attend Anger Management 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DOMESTIC ABUSE SURCHARGE:  $100.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.

Appeal rights given.
